ous. Onto the roof at cow corner. And he follows it up with another!</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52e22907e4b065f7ddbb845e\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-01-24T08:52:16.498Z\">8.52am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">19th over: Australia 96-1 (Finch 58, Wade 22)</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Ravi Bopara comes into the attack for the first time. Wade swings wildly at the first&nbsp;and mistimes it into the turf, but the second is a&nbsp;miserable&nbsp;leg-side effort&nbsp;that gets clipped down to the finest of fine legs for four, Wade's first boundary. A drive for a single from Finch brings up the 50 partnership (from 72 balls).</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52e22815e4b065f7ddbb845c\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-01-24T08:49:03.267Z\">8.49am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">18th over: Australia 90-1 (Finch 57, Wade 17)</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Tredwell is bowling very neatly, and concedes only three runs&nbsp;, but Wade is killing the buzz of this run chase. For him it hasn't&nbsp;really been a chase at all. More of a run-amble. A run-wander. A run-mooch.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52e226e7e4b00f28d73d318d\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-01-24T08:45:07.255Z\">8.45am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">17th over: Australia 87-1 (Finch 56, Wade 15)</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Bresnan steams in once more.&nbsp;Finch dabs away to bring up his half century, rather a two-tone affair and you sense he'll not tolerate this understated mood for very long … and indeed from the last ball of the over he goes high over Bresnan's head for another six. In a way England shouldn't mind that <i>too</i> much – it's a sign that they're bowling tightly enough to make him forc