 I will add my voice to those who believe <a href=\"http://fifthdown.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/01/30/pro-bowl-is-missing-a-skills-competition/\">a skills competition, if done well, would be infinitely more entertaining than what we have right now</a>.&nbsp;</span></p><p>As for this week’s Talkboard, instead of the usual format, we have gathered together a round-up of some of this week’s big stories. At the bottom of this article you will also find a look ahead to the coverage you can expect from us during Super Bowl week. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>And of course, this blog also gives us a place to update you on our Pick the Playoffs competition. I will post the full standings below the line shortly, but for now I can tell you that <b>donwendy2</b>, <b>gregGraffin</b>, <b>thedarrenhudson</b>, <b>ToffeeDan1</b> and <b>YorkiePoo</b> currently share first place with nine correct picks out of 10 each so far.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>And such exceptional postseason form has also been enough to confirm <b>thedarrenhudson</b> as our overall champion. Having already finished top of the Pick Six standings during the regular season, he now stands two clear at the top of the combined table with just one game left to go. Do join me in doffing your caps to a deserving champion; 72 correct picks so far out of a possible 112 so far takes some doing. </p><h2>&nbsp;<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">In the news</span></h2><p>&nbsp;<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">•&nbsp;No one player has dominated the headlines this week more than Richard Sherman, who if nothing else certainly did a good job of stealing the spotlight with his animated post-game interview following Seattle’s win over San Francisco in the NFC Championship Game. Since then the US sports media have been drawn into a week-long conversation about villains, post-game interviews and, of course, race.</span></p><p>Sherman himself tackled the latter&nbsp;subject head-on during a press conference on Thursday, responding to a question about how it felt to be called a ‘thug’ by saying:</p><blockquote class=\"quoted\"><p>The only reason it bothers me is because it seems like it's the accepted way of calling somebody the n-word nowadays. It's like everybody else says the n-word, and then they say thug, and, 'Oh, that's fine.’ That’s where it takes me aback and it’s kinda disappointing, because what's the definition of a thug, really?<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">… There was a hockey game where they didn't even play hockey. They just threw the puck aside and started fighting. I saw that and I said, 'Oh, man, I'm the thug? What’s going on? Geez.</span></p></blockquote> <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4oL01_au6T0\"                                                                                > <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"345\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/4oL01_au6T0?wmode=opaque&feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe> </figure>","headline":"NFL Talkboard: Super Bowl round-up","trailText":"<b>Paolo Bandini:&nbsp;</b>\n\n<!--StartFragment-->This week's big NFL stories, ahead of the Pro Bowl and just over a week away from Super Bowl XLVIII&nbsp;<!--EndFragment-->","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"theguardian.com","showInRelatedContent":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3m65x","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/1/24/1390525686151/91d1ffa9-ef5a-4f92-8cfd-4e4d45f0b761-140x84.jpeg","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/1/24/1390525686151/91d1ffa9-ef5a-4f92-8cfd-4e4d45f0b761-140x84.jpeg","wordcount":"1","commentable":"true","internalContentCode":"427897700","allowUgc":"false","internalComposerCode":"52e1b754e4b0532c050965d0","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Paolo Bandini in Missouri","newspaperEditionDate":"2014-01-24T00:00:00Z","inte