ith England in 2012.</p><p>He is one of the newcomers and he is joined by the Bath back Anthony Watson, Exeter centre Sam Hill, Saints prop Alex Waller, Harlequins lock Charlie Matthews, flanker Luke Wallace, and Exeter No8 Dave Ewers.</p><p>There is also a start for England elite squad member Freddie Burns, with the Gloucester fly-half named as Saxons vice-captain.</p><p></p><h2>England Saxons team to play Ireland Wolfhounds at Gloucester</h2><p>E Daly (Wasps); A Watson (Bath), M Hopper (Harlequins), S Hill (Exeter), C Sharples (Gloucester); F Burns (Gloucester), J Simpson (Wasps); A Waller (Northampton), J George (Saracens), T Mercey (Northampton), C Matthews (Harlequins), G Kruis (Saracens), C Clark (Northampton, capt), L Wallace (Harlequins), D Ewers (Exeter).</p><p><strong>Replacements:</strong> D Ward (Harlequins), N Catt (Bath), S Wilson (Newcastle), E Stooke (Gloucester), S Dickinson (Northampton), D Lewis (Exeter), H Slade (Exeter), R Miller (Sale Sharks).</p>","headline":"Calum Clark will captain England Saxons against Ireland Wolfhounds","trailText":"Northampton's flanker Calum Clark will lead an England Saxons side containing seven debutants against Ireland Wolfhounds at Gloucester on Saturday","newspaperPageNumber":"7","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"The Guardian","showInRelatedContent":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3m6v9","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Sport/Pix/pictures/2014/1/23/1390520238489/Calum-Clark-006.jpg","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Sport/Pix/pictures/2014/1/23/1390520238489/Calum-Clark-006.jpg","wordcount":"258","commentable":"false","internalContentCode":"427873783","allowUgc":"false","internalOctopusCode":"8599125","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Press Association","newspaperEditionDate":"2014-01-24T00:00:00Z","internalPageCode":"2031732","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-01-26T22:28:06Z"},"rights":{"syndicatable":false,"subscri